<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAILOR DIES AFTER MOTORCYCLE HITS TRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A sailor was killed Sunday afternoon in La Jolla after losing control of his 
motorcycle and hitting a parked truck, San Diego police said. 
</P>
<P>
Aaron Vegter, 18, died at Scripps Memorial Hospital shortly after the incident 
in the 2700 block of Torrey Pines Road, said Lt. Bob Stinson. 
</P>
<P>
Vegter was not wearing a helmet while driving his 1989 Yamaha, a coroner's 
deputy said. 
</P>
<P>
A passenger, Caesar Motta, was wearing a helmet, and sustained only minor 
bruises in the accident, the deputy said. Motta was treated at Scripps and 
released. 
</P>
<P>
Police said they were unsure what caused Vegter to lose control of his 
motorcycle. 
</P>
