MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Claudia Puig, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two more TV news troupes are joining those of the three networks and CNN this 
week in covering the economic summit conference in Paris: cable-TV's Financial 
News Network and its rival, NBC-owned CNBC. The latter is dispatching five 
staffers from its London bureau for live morning and afternoon reports from 
Paris during the conference on Thursday, Friday and on Monday. New York-based 
FNN is sending a team of seven, including anchors Bill Griffeth) and Doug 
Ramsey. The Paris conference is the first major overseas event covered live by 
CNBC, which only began operations three months ago. FNN says it covered last 
year's economic summit conference in Toronto. Claudia Puig 
</P>
