BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gas Prices Edge Downward: Gasoline prices fell nearly two cents per gallon in 
June, defying the historical trend toward higher prices during the summer, but 
still registering 18 cents more than at the first of the year. A survey of 
12,000 gasoline stations across the country found the nationwide average for 
all grades of gasoline with taxes included was $1.1676 per gallon, said Trilby 
Lundberg, publisher of the Lundberg Letter, an industry trade publication. The 
average price of $1.1676 was a drop of about two-thirds of a cent from the last 
survey two weeks earlier. 
</P>
