<P>
CHINA HARDENS CRACKDOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China's new hard-line leadership, consolidating its crackdown on pro-democracy 
activists, has issued sweeping orders adding political crimes to legal 
violations and specifying punishments from imprisonment to execution. The 
orders, in a circular issued over the weekend by the Communist Party Politburo 
and the State Council, China's Cabinet, are seen as preparation for tough legal 
action against thousands of people being rounded up nationwide by security 
forces. Meanwhile, an editorial in the People's Daily, the official party 
newspaper, accused the United States and other foreign forces of harboring a 
"wild ambition" to subvert communism and using political and economic weapons 
to support that goal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
