</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BLASTS ROCK TOWN IN INDIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW DELHI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two explosions rocked the town of Leh in northern Jammu-Kashmir state Sunday, 
two days after clashes between Buddhists and Muslims injured at least 25 
people, news reports said. No one was injured in the explosions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
EXPLOSIONS -- INDIA 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA071089-0069 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 80461 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 10, 1989, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part 1; Page 14; Column 1; National Desk 
