<P>
FIREFIGHTER DIES IN BIG SUR BLAZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One firefighter battling an arson blaze near Big Sur died instantly when a tree 
fell on him and six others suffered injuries in the accident, state Department 
of Forestry officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred Sunday night when a 7-member crew from the California 
Department of Corrections was building a fire line, said CDF spokeswoman Lynda 
Parks. The victims were evacuated by ambulance and two military helicopters, 
she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
