<P>
MCCAW CELLULAR LOWERS BID FOR LIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KIRKLAND, Wash. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
McCaw Cellular Communications Inc. said today it had lowered its bid for LIN 
Broadcasting Corp. to $110 from $120 a share after a court decision that 
rejected LIN's claim it had the right to buy cellular telephone interests in 
two key markets. 
</P>
<P>
The current bid would value LIN at just under $6 billion, about $500 million 
lower than its earlier $6.5-billion offer. 
</P>
<P>
McCaw, the country's largest cellular telephone service company, also said its 
tender offer for New York-based LIN had been extended one day to midnight July 
21. All other terms and conditions of the offer remain unchanged, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
