<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
KNICKS HIRE JACKSON, 33, AS COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Knicks hired Stu Jackson as head coach of the team today, ignoring 
questions about his inexperience. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson, 33, a Knicks assistant under Rick Pitino the last two years, has not 
had a previous head coaching job at any level. He is now the youngest coach in 
the NBA. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson's inexperience will be offset by two assistants with acknowledged 
skills in dealing with players -- Paul Silas and Ernie Grunfeld. Silas is a 
former coach of the San Diego Clippers and a star forward for the Hawks, 
Celtics and SuperSonics. Grunfeld was the team's radio analyst the last two 
seasons after retiring as a Knicks player. 
</P>
</TEXT>
