<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
ROMANIAN WOMAN RUNS RECORD MILE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICE, France 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paula Ivan of Romania set a world record today in the women's mile with a time 
of 4:15.62 at the Nikaia IAAF Mobil Grand Prix Grand Prix track and field meet. 
</P>
<P>
Ivan, the Olympic 1,500-meter champion, bettered the mark of 4:16.71 set by 
American Mary Slaney in August, 1985, in Zurich. 
</P>
<P>
Ivan ran alone the final two laps. Her splits for the quarter miles were 63 
seconds, 2:01.1 and 3:12.6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Game Story; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA071089-0115 </DOCNO>
